fields.customfield_10312:
# When anyone replies to an ad, the person is automatically subscribed to an "Automated Recommendation" campaign
 # Valid for MX and AR
 # The subscription will be based on exact matches to the following criteria in the description
 # This ticket depends on front end ticket of "Automated Recommendation" emails  ULIVZ-34857
fields.description:
As a buyer, I would like to have triggered emails sent to me based on my replies to ads so that I don't have to do the search / or subscribe the Saved Alerts myself.

 

-----------

Criteria for matching the triggered email:
 # Level 2 location (e.g. [https://www.vivanuncios.com.mx/s-renta-inmuebles/zapopan/departamento/v1c1098l14828a1pop1]) (eg. Cape Town); (L0 = all country, L1 = state, L2 = city; we want to use city here)
 # Leaf level category (e.g. [https://www.gumtree.co.za/s-cars-bakkies/krugersdorp/v1c9077l3100384p1])
 # Exact match in price for "free" "negotiable" or non-numerical price points
 # For prices with value, use a 10% bracket. If the ad I replied to is $10,000, then the notification is set for $9,000 - $11,000.
 # Besides, also matches in attributes for the following category ads:

[Autos and motorcycles]
 # Same Car Make 
 # Same Car Model 

[Property]
 # Dwelling Type
 # Bedrooms (#) 

[Flat Share & House Share]

      1. Available From: use 1 month bracket.  If the ad I replied to is December, then the notification is set for November -January.

      2. Preferred Gender: exact match 

[Job]

      1. Job Type (full time/part time/contract/intern etc.)

      2. Take off the price criteria for this category.  

 

[All Other]
 # Make and model match when the categories have them, such as cell phone or computer
 # Other categories just use leaf category and L2 location.
fields.summary: Test PHP and C++ drivers with latest C Driver release or release candidate

comments.body:
Initial solution:
1. Send an Kafka event when reply Email.
2. On event, run logic to decide whether to save a special search and save it if any.
QA estimation: 3. Based on assumption that when replying Email, a saved search with automated recommendation type will be saved to MongoDB.

Thanks to [~jitong] for providing the required attribute names. SEO url building for make and model attributes are already implemented. So not listing here.

Available From: AvailabilityStartDate
Dwelling Type: DwellingType
Preferred Gender: PreferredGender
Job Type: JobType
Bedrooms (#): NumberBedrooms

Copying a thread from Slack:

Mervyn Ollie [7:54 PM]
Are the attribute requirements per category?
Eg. For the `Available From` attribute, is it only required for the `[Flat Share & House Share]` category.
If another category has the `Available From` attribute, do we match the attribute? (edited)
Would it be ok to add this criteria for all categories having this attribute?

Eric Cheung [2:57 PM]
Yes - it would be ok to add this criteria for all cateogries having this attribute.

[~homer] The AvailabilityStartDate attribute is not indexed in solr. Means we cannot search by AvailabilityStartDate. So I will omit this attribute when building the seo url. Please create a separate ticket to index this attribute first if needed.

Responding to your note on here [~leiychen]  Noted.

[~john] Tagging you to let you know that Alice said "AvailabilityStartDate" cannot be used for this purpose yet. We can file a different ticket later if needed.
[~homer][~leiychen] Thank you Alice and Eric. Will create a separate ticket if needed later.
As confirmed with [~john], there is a cap=1 for automated recommendation email. And the last reply will win. Means we need to update the automated recommendation when there is a new reply.

There are two pieces of code changes for this ticket:
1. AC-ULIVZ-33799-AR-INTG in bolt-platform, no opened PR.
2. AC-ULIVZ-35280 in replyts2-ebayk-message-center, PR is https://github.corp.ebay.com/ecg-global/replyts2-ebayk-message-center/pull/3.

Assigning this to Facebook.

 

[~leiychen] [~john]  Can you review this ticket? I'm not sure if it's a duplicate to the other tickets.

# When anyone replies to an ad, the person is automatically subscribed to an "Automated Recommendation" campaign
 # Valid for MX and AR
 # The subscription will be based on exact matches to the following criteria in the description
 # This ticket depends on front end ticket of "Automated Recommendation" emails  ULIVZ-34857

items.fromString:
As a buyer, I would like to have triggered emails sent to me based on my replies to ads so that I don't have to do the search / or subscribe the Saved Alerts myself.

-----------

Criteria for matching the triggered email:
 # Level 2 location (e.g. [https://www.vivanuncios.com.mx/s-renta-inmuebles/zapopan/departamento/v1c1098l14828a1pop1]) (eg. Cape Town); (L0 = all country, L1 = state, L2 = city; we want to use city here)
 # Leaf level category (e.g. [https://www.gumtree.co.za/s-cars-bakkies/krugersdorp/v1c9077l3100384p1])
 # Exact match in price for "free" "negotiable" or non-numerical price points
 # For prices with value, use a 10% bracket. If the ad I replied to is $10,000, then the notification is set for $9,000 - $11,000.
 # Matches in attributes based on below:

[Autos and motorcycles]
 # Same Car Make 
 # Same Car Model 

[Property]
 # Dwelling Type
 # Bedrooms (#) 

[Flat Share & House Share]

      1. Available From: use 1 month bracket.  If the ad I replied to is December, then the notification is set for November -January.

      2. Preferred Gender: exact match 

[Job]

      1. Job Type 

[All Other]
 # Make and model match when the categories have them, such as cell phone or computer
